@startuml cross_storage_device_vertical_tiering
title Cross-Storage Device Vertical Tiering Architecture\nLUN scales up across devices without disconnecting consumers

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam roundcorner 6
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #EAF2F8
  BorderColor #2874A6
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FDEBD0
  DiamondBorderColor #B9770E
}

|Cloud Service Consumer|
start
:Issue storage requests;

|Storage Service Gateway|
:Forward requests to
primary (lower-capacity)
cloud storage device;

|Automated Scaling Listener|
:Monitor request volume
against thresholds;
if (Threshold reached?) then (yes)
  :Notify storage management program;
else (no)
  :Continue monitoring;
  stop
endif

|Storage Management Program|
:Categorize storage by
device performance;
:Call LUN migration to
move LUN to secondary
(higher-capacity) device;

|LUN Migration|
:Copy LUN to secondary device
(original remains active during transfer);
:Verify destination copy;

|Storage Service Gateway|
:Redirect requests to
new cloud storage device;

|Storage Management Program|
:Delete LUN from
lower-capacity device;

|Automated Scaling Listener|
:Monitor sustained demand
on higher-capacity device;
stop

note right
  Service interruption is prevented:
  there is never a disconnection
  during the transfer.
end note

note left
  Supporting mechanisms:
  Audit Monitor (data-relocation
  legality and policy checks),
  Cloud Usage Monitor,
  Pay-Per-Use Monitor (source
  and destination accounting).
end note

@enduml
